#. <section class="sutta" id="an3.2"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an3.2:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 3"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 3"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.2:0.2"
msgid "1. Bālavagga"
msgstr "1. Fools"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an3.2:0.3"
msgid "2. Lakkhaṇasutta"
msgstr "2. Characteristics"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.102"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
#. VAR: apadānasobhanī → apadānasobhinī (bj) | apadāne sobhati (s1-3, km, pts1)
#. VAR: paññāti → paññā (s1-3) | paññatti (?)
msgctxt "an3.2:1.1"
msgid ""
"“Kammalakkhaṇo, bhikkhave, bālo, kammalakkhaṇo paṇḍito, apadānasobhanī "
"paññāti."
msgstr ""
"“A fool is characterized by their deeds; an astute person is characterized "
"by their deeds. And wisdom is evident in its outcome."

msgctxt "an3.2:1.2"
msgid "Tīhi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato bālo veditabbo."
msgstr "A fool is known by three things."

msgctxt "an3.2:1.3"
msgid "Katamehi tīhi?"
msgstr "What three?"

msgctxt "an3.2:1.4"
msgid "Kāyaduccaritena, vacīduccaritena, manoduccaritena."
msgstr "Bad conduct by way of body, speech, and mind."

msgctxt "an3.2:1.5"
msgid "Imehi kho, bhikkhave, tīhi dhammehi samannāgato bālo veditabbo."
msgstr "These are the three things by which a fool is known."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an3.2:2.1"
msgid "Tīhi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato paṇḍito veditabbo."
msgstr "An astute person is known by three things."

msgctxt "an3.2:2.2"
msgid "Katamehi tīhi?"
msgstr "What three?"

msgctxt "an3.2:2.3"
msgid "Kāyasucaritena, vacīsucaritena, manosucaritena."
msgstr "Good conduct by way of body, speech, and mind."

msgctxt "an3.2:2.4"
msgid "Imehi kho, bhikkhave, tīhi dhammehi samannāgato paṇḍito veditabbo."
msgstr "These are the three things by which an astute person is known."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an3.2:3.1"
msgid "Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, evaṃ sikkhitabbaṃ:"
msgstr "So you should train like this:"

msgctxt "an3.2:3.2"
msgid ""
"‘yehi tīhi dhammehi samannāgato bālo veditabbo te tayo dhamme "
"abhinivajjetvā, yehi tīhi dhammehi samannāgato paṇḍito veditabbo te tayo "
"dhamme samādāya vattissāmā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘We will reject the three things by which a fool is known, and we will "
"undertake and follow the three things by which an astute person is known.’"

msgctxt "an3.2:3.3"
msgid "Evañhi vo, bhikkhave, sikkhitabban”ti."
msgstr "That’s how you should train.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an3.2:3.4"
msgid "Dutiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
